## Setting 5: Three-Stone and Baguette (from $2,720)

[![Emerald cut diamond three-stone ring in yellow gold](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/505082/505082_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

The three-stone setting pairs the center emerald cut with two side stones. For an emerald cut, the best side stones are baguettes or smaller emerald cuts — shapes that echo the step-cut structure of the center stone. Round side stones work but they introduce a visual contrast that draws the eye to the side stones rather than letting them support the center.

Baguette side stones are ideal. A baguette has the same step facet structure as an emerald cut. When set next to an emerald cut center, both stones catch the light in the same way — a unified, coordinated look. The combination is classic, architectural, and distinctive.

The three-stone setting also adds carat weight to the total look without the cost of a larger center stone. A 1ct center flanked by two 0.30ct baguettes reads visually larger than a 1ct solitaire.

