## Vintage and Art Deco Settings Worth Considering

[![Emerald cut diamond ring in vintage-style yellow gold setting](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501830/501830_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box4_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Vintage and Art Deco settings can work well for an emerald cut — with one condition: the vintage detail must stay on the shank, not around the stone. Gallery rails with milgrain or twisted wire add character to the band. Filigree on the shoulder adds texture. Neither breaks the rectangular outline of the center stone as long as the detail doesn't climb to the top visual plane.

Art Deco settings from the 1920s and 1930s were originally designed around step-cut stones. The geometric ornamentation of that era — bold lines, symmetry, angular motifs — is a natural match for the emerald cut. Modern Art Deco-inspired settings pick up these same visual themes.

